You can create custom selector functions:
# Create a selector that matches documented functions only
my_selector = sym -&gt; begin
    obj = getfield(MyModule, sym)
    return obj isa Function && hasmethod(obj, Tuple{})
end



Extend the theme with custom CSS/SCSS:
theme = ThemeConfig(
    bootswatch = "flatly",
    custom_css = """
    .my-custom-class {
        color: red;
    }
    """
)

Add custom CSS rules:
theme = ThemeConfig(
    bootswatch = "flatly",
    custom_css = """
    /* Custom navbar gradient */
    .navbar {
        background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%) !important;
    }

    /* Custom code block style */
    pre code {
        border-radius: 8px;
    }

    /* Highlight callouts */
    .callout-note {
        border-left-color: #007bff;
    }
    """
)

For advanced customization, use SCSS:
theme = ThemeConfig(
    custom_scss = """
    $primary: #667eea;
    $link-color: #764ba2;
    $border-radius: 0.5rem;
    """
)

get_objects_from_module






docblock





```{julia}

get_objects_from_module(m::Module) -&gt; Vector{Docs.Binding}
```
Get all documented objects from a module using Base.Docs.meta(). Returns a vector of Docs.Binding objects (preserving module context).

